1
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:11,600
<i>- Enriquez.
- Can I talk to you?</i>

2
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:12,933
<i>Chief, can it just be
the two of us?</i>

3
00:00:13,067 --> 00:00:14,700
<i> I talked to Selena yesterday.</i>

4
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:18,133
<i>Sonny said that Amo had a spy
here at the station.</i>

5
00:00:18,267 --> 00:00:19,300
<i> According to Daga's companion,</i>

6
00:00:19,433 --> 00:00:21,033
<i>a policeman took Daga
away last night.</i>

7
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:22,167
<i> I have a strong feeling</i>

8
00:00:22,300 --> 00:00:24,700
<i>that Conde is Amo's henchman
at the station.</i>

9
00:00:25,967 --> 00:00:26,967
<i> Bok, what's going on?</i>

10
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:28,767
<i> I suspended him indefinitely.</i>

11
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:30,867
<i> There's someone outside, Amo.</i>

12
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,633
<i>He is waiting for you.
He is looking for you.</i>

13
00:00:32,767 --> 00:00:33,433
<i> Tonyo?</i>

14
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,300
<i>It's exciting here in Calabari.</i>

15
00:00:35,433 --> 00:00:37,167
<i>What if I transfer
to Station 12?</i>

16
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:41,767
<i> Charlie?</i>

17
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:43,033
<i> Bobby...</i>

18
00:00:43,167 --> 00:00:44,400
<i>We're here because we're
investigating human trafficking.</i>

19
00:00:44,533 --> 00:00:46,400
<i>Our lead brought us here
to Calabari.</i>

20
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:48,500
<i>I have nothing to do with all
that.</i>

21
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:52,333
<i>You may not be a bad person,
but you are still a bad father.</i>

22
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:53,533
<i> I know.</i>

23
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:54,967
<i>I can't change that,
but I want to make it up to you.</i>

24
00:00:55,100 --> 00:00:56,267
<i> Give me a job.</i>

25
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:57,400
<i> Make me your bodyguard.</i>

26
00:00:57,533 --> 00:00:58,733
<i> Who are you? You're a cop!</i>

27
00:00:59,867 --> 00:01:01,667
<i> Tonyo! That's enough!</i>

28
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:03,833
<i>That's Roman,
my head of security.</i>

29
00:01:03,967 --> 00:01:05,400
<i> Tonyo, my son.</i>

30
00:01:08,067 --> 00:01:09,767
Tonyo, here's the ice.

31
00:01:10,967 --> 00:01:12,000
I'm fine.

32
00:01:15,033 --> 00:01:17,000
What happened to you guys that
you almost shot each other?

33
00:01:19,633 --> 00:01:22,033
Your dog was the first
to threaten me.

34
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:24,000
Oh, wait, wait. Relax, easy.

35
00:01:24,133 --> 00:01:26,467
I pointed a gun at you
because I don't know you.

36
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:28,500
How would I know what's your
business with Amo?

37
00:01:28,633 --> 00:01:30,033
How would I also know
that he's your son?

38
00:01:30,167 --> 00:01:32,100
Oh, that's enough,
that's enough.

39
00:01:32,233 --> 00:01:35,000
I'm sorry, Tonyo,
he was just being careful.

40
00:01:35,133 --> 00:01:37,867
You'd better come inside.
I prepared food.

41
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:38,867
Let's talk there.

42
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,667
I'll just come back.

43
00:01:40,833 --> 00:01:42,467
I'll start tomorrow.

44
00:01:42,600 --> 00:01:45,367
Hey, wait. What's starting?
Starting what?

45
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:48,700
He's going to work for me
as my personal bodyguard.

46
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:51,400
I don't want to happen what had
happened earlier.

47
00:01:52,433 --> 00:01:54,067
Okay, son, be careful.

48
00:01:59,567 --> 00:02:01,433
Are you sure, Amo?

49
00:02:02,833 --> 00:02:04,500
He's a cop.

50
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:07,167
After all this time,
he's been ignoring me,

51
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:09,167
this is the first time he has
come to me.

52
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:12,467
I'm not going to miss
this opportunity.

53
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,533
Amo, let me just remind you,
okay?

54
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:19,367
Even if we turn the world upside
down, he's still a cop.

55
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:23,833
Even if we turn the world upside
down, he's still my son.

56
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:32,167
What, Bobby?

57
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:33,800
Tonyo was suspended?

58
00:02:34,967 --> 00:02:36,667
So what now? Are you happy now?

59
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:37,600
No!

60
00:02:37,733 --> 00:02:38,900
You don't miss him?

61
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:40,333
Not either!

62
00:02:40,467 --> 00:02:41,967
You're not feeling guilty?

63
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:46,533
I had nothing to do with his
suspension.

64
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:47,533
What do you mean you had nothing
to do?

65
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:48,833
Well,

66
00:02:48,967 --> 00:02:51,300
weren't you the one insisting
that he might be the spy?

67
00:02:51,433 --> 00:02:54,733
Maybe your Boss believed you,
so he was suspended.

68
00:02:54,867 --> 00:02:56,433
Poor Tonyo.

69
00:02:56,567 --> 00:03:00,400
His girlfriend died,
and he was suspended from work!

70
00:03:00,533 --> 00:03:02,200
He might be drinking, Mar.

71
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:03,333
You're terrible, Bobby!

72
00:03:03,467 --> 00:03:04,667
You're terrible!
You should feel guilty!

73
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:06,333
Maybe something bad happened
to him!

74
00:03:06,467 --> 00:03:07,733
If it were me,
I'd feel guilty about that.

75
00:03:07,867 --> 00:03:08,933
You fool!

76
00:03:09,067 --> 00:03:10,767
My granddaughter is not guilty,
hey!

77
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:14,300
There's a reason why
it happened to him.

78
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:16,600
He's at fault,
not my grandchild!

79
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:18,000
She's not guilty.

80
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,200
My grandchild is not guilty.

81
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:21,633
Grandmother...

82
00:03:21,767 --> 00:03:22,633
guilty.

83
00:03:28,067 --> 00:03:29,933
I can't help it.

84
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:50,600
He's rejecting my call.

85
00:03:50,733 --> 00:03:51,933
Of course!

86
00:03:54,733 --> 00:03:56,867
I told you not to blame
my grandchild!

87
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,267
Because I'm going
to reject it too.

88
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,733
Yes, me too.

89
00:04:34,467 --> 00:04:36,100
Morning!

90
00:04:36,233 --> 00:04:37,267
Let's have coffee.

91
00:04:44,933 --> 00:04:47,233
It seems like we woke up
on the wrong side of the bed.

92
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,700
We still have a lot
of supporters there.

93
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:57,667
Okay.

94
00:04:58,700 --> 00:04:59,300
Tonyo.

95
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:00,367
Good Morning, Amo.

96
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:02,267
Come with me on the campaign.

97
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:05,300
Amo, I'm just reminding you,
okay.

98
00:05:05,433 --> 00:05:06,733
A police officer's job
is different

99
00:05:06,867 --> 00:05:07,967
from being a bodyguard.

100
00:05:09,167 --> 00:05:10,600
I can do this, Roman.

101
00:05:10,733 --> 00:05:13,900
Did you know that yesterday,
someone pointed a gun at me?

102
00:05:14,033 --> 00:05:17,167
I was able to knock him down
using a hose.

103
00:05:17,300 --> 00:05:18,233
What did you say?

104
00:05:18,367 --> 00:05:19,900
Oh, that's enough,
that's enough.

105
00:05:21,267 --> 00:05:25,167
Roman, just get our tarpaulins
from the supplier, okay?

106
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:28,533
Oh, come on, come on.

107
00:05:28,667 --> 00:05:29,467
Let's go.

108
00:05:32,067 --> 00:05:33,167
Bye, Roman.

109
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:38,600
Ma'am Enriquez,
do you want some?

110
00:05:38,733 --> 00:05:40,833
Why isn't Sir Tonyo answering?

111
00:05:40,967 --> 00:05:42,600
How about you?
Is he replying to you?

112
00:05:42,733 --> 00:05:44,600
He's not answering me, Ma'am.

113
00:05:44,733 --> 00:05:46,033
What happened to him?

114
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:50,100
Maybe he blames me
for his suspension.

115
00:05:51,467 --> 00:05:53,000
If you're restless, Ma'am,

116
00:05:53,133 --> 00:05:55,600
do you want us to drop by
at his house later?

117
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:01,400
Amo!

118
00:06:01,533 --> 00:06:02,367
How are you?

119
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,200
Don't forget me.

120
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:05,833
Oh, you too.

121
00:06:06,867 --> 00:06:08,933
For Calabari, let's be together.

122
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:11,800
I'm grateful to all of you
because,

123
00:06:11,933 --> 00:06:16,867
despite the successive blows
and accusations against me,

124
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,733
you're still here to support me!

125
00:06:19,867 --> 00:06:21,333
You've got our votes, Amo!

126
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,600
- Amo!
- Amo!

127
00:06:26,733 --> 00:06:29,400
Oh, again, I thank you.

128
00:06:29,533 --> 00:06:30,667
And you know,

129
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:35,067
the support I see you giving me
is enough for us to continue

130
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:37,133
the fight for Calabari!

131
00:06:39,533 --> 00:06:41,833
- Amo!
- Amo!

132
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,467
You're an actor, Amo!

133
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:47,133
You're such a good pretender,
Amo.

134
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:52,000
Take Amo away, come on!

135
00:06:53,267 --> 00:06:54,200
Tonyo!

136
00:07:16,133 --> 00:07:17,367
Help!

137
00:07:19,233 --> 00:07:20,667
Move over! Move!

138
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,067
Hey, what's that?

139
00:07:36,167 --> 00:07:37,167
Let go of that!

140
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:38,833
I said let go of that!

141
00:07:42,667 --> 00:07:45,000
Noble, I'll take care of this!

142
00:08:05,467 --> 00:08:06,600
Lieutenant Conde...

143
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:24,333
Ces...

144
00:08:26,867 --> 00:08:29,033
Lieutenant Garcia, hi.

145
00:08:31,033 --> 00:08:32,367
I knew it,

146
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:35,833
that's why you haven't been
replying to texts,

147
00:08:35,967 --> 00:08:38,433
it's because you wanted
to surprise me here.

148
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:41,767
I'm so touched.

149
00:08:44,267 --> 00:08:50,367
Actually, I'm here to deliver
the medicolegal report.

150
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:53,533
Sorry, I was so busy that
I couldn't reply to you.

151
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:56,067
It's okay.

152
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,433
I forgive you.

153
00:08:59,233 --> 00:09:03,333
Ces, the important thing is,
we're not busy anymore.

154
00:09:03,467 --> 00:09:06,533
Do you want to have dinner
tonight?

155
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:09,267
Because tomorrow,
I'm super busy.

156
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:11,133
Tonight is the best night.

157
00:09:12,300 --> 00:09:14,767
Too bad, I'm free tomorrow.

158
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:15,967
I'm busy today.

159
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:18,967
I knew it.

160
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:22,167
No, actually, I'm free tomorrow.

161
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:24,000
I'm busy tonight.

162
00:09:24,133 --> 00:09:27,800
You know, I like your style.
You're playing hard to get.

163
00:09:27,967 --> 00:09:29,100
So what?

164
00:09:29,233 --> 00:09:32,233
Can I make a reservation?
I have a favorite restaurant.

165
00:09:32,367 --> 00:09:33,500
Let's dine in there.

166
00:09:33,633 --> 00:09:36,767
- Wait, wait.
- Hello?

167
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:38,700
Lieutenant Garcia, wait, wait.

168
00:09:38,833 --> 00:09:40,933
7 PM. Yeah, yeah, I got it.

169
00:09:41,067 --> 00:09:43,300
The woman's ID
is Bernarda Salazar.

170
00:09:43,433 --> 00:09:46,467
According to records,
she just got out of prison.

171
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:51,000
Why would she want
to attack Amo?

172
00:09:51,133 --> 00:09:53,500
She wants to seek revenge
for the death of her son.

173
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,633
Bok,

174
00:09:55,767 --> 00:09:57,067
Daga is her son.

175
00:10:01,933 --> 00:10:03,267
Thank you, Buddy.

176
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:05,467
Okay, I'll go ahead.
I need to attend to something.

177
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,333
Okay.

178
00:10:08,933 --> 00:10:09,733
Sir...

179
00:10:12,867 --> 00:10:14,467
Sir Tonyo...

180
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:16,100
Are you mad at me?

181
00:10:18,733 --> 00:10:19,767
I just wanted to say

182
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:21,867
that I had nothing to do with
your suspension.

183
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:24,833
Okay.

184
00:10:25,933 --> 00:10:26,867
If you say so.

185
00:10:29,367 --> 00:10:30,100
Sir...

186
00:10:36,100 --> 00:10:36,767
How are you?

187
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:40,067
What are you doing here?

188
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,033
Working.

189
00:10:44,167 --> 00:10:45,300
Work?

190
00:10:45,433 --> 00:10:46,300
Where, Sir?

191
00:10:47,667 --> 00:10:48,567
Son!

192
00:10:50,633 --> 00:10:51,733
Are you okay?

193
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:54,100
I'm okay.

194
00:10:54,233 --> 00:10:56,633
Thank you for saving me.

195
00:10:56,767 --> 00:10:59,300
It's a good thing I got you
as my bodyguard.

196
00:11:02,467 --> 00:11:03,867
It's just work, Father.

197
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:07,533
Amo, come on, let's eat first.

198
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,100
Yes. Okay.

199
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:13,700
Sir,

200
00:11:15,267 --> 00:11:16,867
are you Amo's bodyguard?

201
00:11:22,667 --> 00:11:25,500
It seems Lieutenant Garcia
forced you.

202
00:11:25,633 --> 00:11:27,533
Doc, he's a good boy.

203
00:11:27,667 --> 00:11:29,533
Yes, Doc.
He doesn't have rabies.

204
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:33,867
Gosh.

205
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,900
Okay, we made reservations
already.

206
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:38,533
Okay, fine.

207
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:41,233
Ah, wait.

208
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:43,800
Is it true that Lieutenant Conde
was suspended?

209
00:11:43,933 --> 00:11:45,000
Why?

210
00:11:45,133 --> 00:11:47,900
You know, let's save it
for tomorrow.

211
00:11:48,033 --> 00:11:50,600
Let's talk about that,
but the important thing is,

212
00:11:50,733 --> 00:11:52,567
our schedule is confirmed.

213
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:53,733
Oh, okay.

214
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:55,367
I need to get back to work.

215
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:56,767
Okay. I'll just go there.

216
00:12:12,100 --> 00:12:13,200
Hello?

217
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:16,033
One of your police officers
is here, Lieutenant Conde.

218
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,267
What's he doing there?

219
00:12:18,733 --> 00:12:19,667
He is Amo's son.

220
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,267
He gave him a job and made him
his bodyguard.

221
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,000
Really?

222
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:25,900
He has so many places to go.
Why here?

223
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,233
I don't know.

224
00:12:28,367 --> 00:12:29,733
Find out, Robles.

225
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:31,800
Find out what his real motive
is.

226
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:32,967
Okay.

227
00:12:33,100 --> 00:12:35,633
I'll drop by later to pick up
my laundry.

228
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:41,000
I'm suspended, right?

229
00:12:41,133 --> 00:12:42,567
I need to earn some money.

230
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,767
Wait a minute, Sir.

231
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:49,567
Do you know the word conflict
of interest?

232
00:12:49,733 --> 00:12:50,867
This is it!

233
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:51,867
Enriquez,

234
00:12:53,167 --> 00:12:55,933
I have no other interest
than myself!

235
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:59,867
Sir, we've been through a lot
to come up with a lead

236
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,167
and a prime suspect.

237
00:13:02,967 --> 00:13:04,800
That's Amo, right?

238
00:13:04,933 --> 00:13:07,067
And now, you'll be working
for him.

239
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:12,133
I don't need to explain anything
to you.

240
00:13:15,567 --> 00:13:16,500
I'm sorry.

241
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:21,067
I didn't mean to overhear what
you were talking about.

242
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:24,900
But, Sergeant Enriquez,
don't take it negatively

243
00:13:25,067 --> 00:13:28,167
that I hired Tonyo
as my bodyguard.

244
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:31,700
Just say, you took advantage of
Lieutenant Conde's suspension!

245
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,233
Enriquez!

246
00:13:33,367 --> 00:13:34,767
You're going too far.

247
00:13:37,067 --> 00:13:39,700
You talk as if you're nice.

248
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:42,100
The reason why I got suspended
is because of you?

249
00:13:43,267 --> 00:13:45,367
Then, now, you're going
to insult my father.

250
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,200
Aren't you happy with what you
did?

251
00:13:49,033 --> 00:13:50,267
Can you leave now?

252
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:54,233
Tonyo, that's enough.

253
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,867
Let's just eat.

254
00:14:11,167 --> 00:14:12,100
Okay.

255
00:14:12,233 --> 00:14:13,767
Thank you, Toliga.

256
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:14,700
Ma'am.

257
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:17,267
You were so good earlier.

258
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:19,300
I almost ran out of breath.

259
00:14:21,533 --> 00:14:22,733
Where did you learn that?

260
00:14:23,933 --> 00:14:24,667
In training.

261
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:28,033
Cool...

262
00:14:29,700 --> 00:14:32,567
I'm sure your mother
is proud of you.

263
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:36,033
My mother is gone.

264
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:41,400
You seem like a nice person.

265
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:44,967
It's just a shame you only
got out for a short while.

266
00:14:46,733 --> 00:14:49,067
You shouldn't have attacked
Amo earlier.

267
00:14:55,833 --> 00:14:58,333
He is the reason why my son
died.

268
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:02,400
He should pay for that,

269
00:15:04,533 --> 00:15:05,333
right?

270
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:10,533
If I had been released earlier,
I would have protected Daga.

271
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:15,000
Even if I had to die,

272
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:19,400
to keep my son alive.

273
00:15:19,533 --> 00:15:20,633
You should understand me.

274
00:15:20,767 --> 00:15:21,800
You're a police officer,

275
00:15:21,933 --> 00:15:27,467
your obligation is to protect
people,

276
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:30,767
especially those who are
important to you, right?

277
00:15:30,900 --> 00:15:33,067
What more, I,
the mother of his child.

278
00:15:49,767 --> 00:15:50,467
Bobby.

279
00:15:51,667 --> 00:15:53,033
Godfather.

280
00:15:53,167 --> 00:15:54,000
Okay, sit down.

281
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:06,200
Godfather, I just brought some
groceries for you.

282
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,867
You shouldn't have gone out
of your way.

283
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:12,600
Godfather, please accept it.

284
00:16:12,733 --> 00:16:18,967
I won't be at peace until
I've done something for you.

285
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:21,400
Sorry if I'm being annoying.

286
00:16:21,533 --> 00:16:24,300
I'm still feeling guilty.

287
00:16:24,433 --> 00:16:25,400
Bobby,

288
00:16:26,833 --> 00:16:28,333
I've forgiven you.

289
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:30,833
I don't want you to carry
that guilt

290
00:16:30,967 --> 00:16:33,733
for the rest of your life
because it's not your fault.

291
00:16:35,133 --> 00:16:38,033
I'm sorry too because I blamed
you.

292
00:16:39,367 --> 00:16:40,767
Thank you, Godfather.

293
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:49,200
Just in case, if you need
anything, just call me.

294
00:16:50,567 --> 00:16:51,500
Thank you.

295
00:16:51,633 --> 00:16:53,133
Thank you.

296
00:16:53,267 --> 00:16:54,900
Dad, where's the...

297
00:16:55,033 --> 00:16:55,800
Reign...

298
00:16:57,733 --> 00:16:59,200
What's she doing here?

299
00:16:59,333 --> 00:17:00,100
Reign, what...

300
00:17:00,233 --> 00:17:01,533
Why are you talking
to that girl?

301
00:17:01,667 --> 00:17:03,967
Reign, Bobby is just saying
hello to us.

302
00:17:05,567 --> 00:17:07,767
Dad and I are not okay
because of you!

303
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:12,733
Your greetings won't make up for
the loss we've had for Mom!

304
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,233
What's that?

305
00:17:17,367 --> 00:17:18,533
Is that from her?

306
00:17:20,133 --> 00:17:22,533
I had that delivered earlier.

307
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:24,267
You know, you'd better go.

308
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:25,633
Go away!

309
00:17:25,767 --> 00:17:27,433
Bobby, go ahead, you can leave.

310
00:17:35,667 --> 00:17:37,867
Bobby, it's getting late.

311
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:38,933
Mister...

312
00:18:09,533 --> 00:18:10,300
<i> Mother,</i>

313
00:18:11,967 --> 00:18:13,533
<i> how are you?</i>

314
00:18:13,667 --> 00:18:19,800
<i>As for me, I am so lost in
so many thoughts and feelings.</i>

315
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:23,800
<i>A while ago, I caught a gang
leader's mother.</i>

316
00:18:23,967 --> 00:18:26,700
<i>She's ready to go to jail
again for her son,</i>

317
00:18:26,833 --> 00:18:29,567
<i>and she's also ready to die
for him.</i>

318
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:32,733
<i>Like what you did when you saved
me before.</i>

319
00:18:32,867 --> 00:18:36,533
<i> I hope it was worth it.</i>

320
00:18:36,667 --> 00:18:38,900
<i> I hope you're proud of me.</i>

321
00:18:39,033 --> 00:18:42,367
<i>Because even though I want
to do the right thing,</i>

322
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:44,633
<i> I still made wrong decisions</i>

323
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:46,900
<i>that affected other people's
lives.</i>

324
00:18:47,033 --> 00:18:50,767
<i>Your greetings won't make up
for the loss of our mother!</i>

325
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:51,900
<i> You're going too far.</i>

326
00:18:52,033 --> 00:18:53,900
<i> You talk as if you're so kind.</i>

327
00:18:54,033 --> 00:18:55,867
<i>That's why I got suspended,
because of you?</i>

328
00:18:56,033 --> 00:18:57,600
<i>And now, you're going
to insult my father.</i>

329
00:18:57,733 --> 00:18:59,133
<i>Aren't you happy with what you
did?</i>

330
00:19:03,567 --> 00:19:04,200
<i> Mother,</i>

331
00:19:05,633 --> 00:19:07,467
<i> please pray for me.</i>

332
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:11,567
<i>I hope I can make up for
my mistakes with these people.</i>

333
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:16,100
<i>And if it's too late,
I hope they can forgive me.</i>

334
00:19:29,333 --> 00:19:34,267
We can't stop Tonyo if he wants
to work for Victor Santiago.

335
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,967
He didn't break any laws.

336
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:38,667
What are you worried about?

337
00:19:40,133 --> 00:19:42,067
That Tonyo would leak
information

338
00:19:43,467 --> 00:19:46,067
because of the case being made
against Amo?

339
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,833
Well, he wouldn't do that.

340
00:19:51,767 --> 00:19:53,367
Sir, I was just thinking,

341
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:57,967
isn't it because of me
that Tonyo ended up there?

342
00:19:58,100 --> 00:19:59,267
Maybe...

343
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:01,100
Maybe I pushed him.

344
00:20:03,033 --> 00:20:03,733
Enriquez,

345
00:20:05,433 --> 00:20:07,733
Conde can make his own
decisions.

346
00:20:07,867 --> 00:20:11,500
Chief, I'm just afraid, maybe if
he stays there long enough,

347
00:20:11,633 --> 00:20:14,367
he'll discover that his father
is a criminal.

348
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:16,100
Maybe he'll get killed there,

349
00:20:16,233 --> 00:20:20,300
or maybe he'll just accept
the wrong system.

350
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:25,133
Chief, can't we just request
a search warrant for you, Amo,

351
00:20:25,267 --> 00:20:28,067
so we can get evidence?

352
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:32,533
We don't have a strong case
to get a search warrant.

353
00:20:32,667 --> 00:20:34,167
That's the thing, Sir.

354
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:37,500
How can we get evidence if we
don't have a search warrant?

355
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:39,333
Enriquez,

356
00:20:40,667 --> 00:20:42,300
just trust the process.

357
00:20:43,533 --> 00:20:46,100
Okay, you can leave now.

358
00:20:47,367 --> 00:20:47,933
Yes, Sir.

359
00:20:57,933 --> 00:20:58,700
Boss?

360
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:05,300
Go ahead.

361
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:16,733
What's that?

362
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:22,433
It's Robles, Conde is indeed
suspended.

363
00:21:22,567 --> 00:21:23,500
So it's true,

364
00:21:23,633 --> 00:21:25,400
he works for his father.

365
00:21:25,533 --> 00:21:26,900
So what do you think of him?

366
00:21:27,033 --> 00:21:28,633
He's still acting like
a police officer.

367
00:21:28,767 --> 00:21:30,533
He could be just working.

368
00:21:30,667 --> 00:21:32,333
But me, me, I'm paranoid.

369
00:21:33,233 --> 00:21:34,867
He could be investigating.

370
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:36,433
In that case,

371
00:21:37,667 --> 00:21:39,567
be careful with your actions.

372
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:41,400
I don't want my plans
to be ruined

373
00:21:41,533 --> 00:21:44,033
by a suspended police officer.

374
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:44,933
Yes, Boss.

375
00:21:47,033 --> 00:21:47,633
Ma'am, coffee.

376
00:21:48,633 --> 00:21:49,533
Thank you.

377
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:53,800
Noble?

378
00:21:54,867 --> 00:21:57,933
Why did Chief say
"Trust the process"?

379
00:21:58,067 --> 00:21:59,567
What does that mean?

380
00:21:59,700 --> 00:22:02,500
Well, trust the process.

381
00:22:02,633 --> 00:22:04,033
What is the process?

382
00:22:05,233 --> 00:22:06,033
What is that?

383
00:22:06,167 --> 00:22:07,600
We'll just wait for the hard
evidence

384
00:22:07,733 --> 00:22:09,567
to land here on our table?

385
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:10,533
There's nothing like that.

386
00:22:11,567 --> 00:22:14,400
So what are we going to do,
Ma'am?

387
00:22:14,533 --> 00:22:16,233
We should be the ones taking
action.

388
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:18,800
You know, Noble,
while Amo is free,

389
00:22:18,933 --> 00:22:21,033
he has time to clear his name.

390
00:22:22,133 --> 00:22:23,933
Noble, help me, okay?

391
00:22:24,067 --> 00:22:25,467
So what are we going to do,
Ma'am?

392
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:26,900
I don't know.

393
00:22:27,033 --> 00:22:28,900
As long as you help me.

394
00:22:29,033 --> 00:22:31,767
Okay, Ma'am, as long as we don't
get in trouble with Chief.

395
00:22:38,433 --> 00:22:40,800
I'm sorry for what happened
yesterday.

396
00:22:41,933 --> 00:22:45,033
That girl and I really don't get
along.

397
00:22:45,167 --> 00:22:46,900
She has an attitude problem.

398
00:22:49,467 --> 00:22:51,433
That's not an issue with me.
That's no problem.

399
00:22:51,567 --> 00:22:54,800
You can't please everyone.

400
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:57,333
Thank you.

401
00:22:58,567 --> 00:23:01,300
My job is to protect you.

402
00:23:03,433 --> 00:23:06,033
That's not why I'm grateful.

403
00:23:07,633 --> 00:23:09,900
Thank you for calling me
"Father".

404
00:23:11,033 --> 00:23:11,600
To be honest,

405
00:23:11,733 --> 00:23:14,067
Roman isn't sure about you

406
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:17,233
because he thinks you might have
a hidden agenda.

407
00:23:17,367 --> 00:23:21,933
But if he only knew what
you did to me yesterday,

408
00:23:23,033 --> 00:23:25,367
I'm sure his doubts would
disappear.

409
00:23:27,967 --> 00:23:28,767
Thank you.

410
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,600
I trust you completely.

411
00:23:34,167 --> 00:23:38,233
And I won't do anything
to break that trust.

412
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:45,400
My landlady is calling.
I'll just answer this.

413
00:23:45,533 --> 00:23:46,600
Oh, okay, okay.

414
00:23:46,733 --> 00:23:49,833
But after that,
follow me upstairs, okay?

415
00:23:49,967 --> 00:23:50,767
Yes I will.

416
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,367
Hello?

417
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:55,667
Ms. Tess.

418
00:23:57,167 --> 00:23:58,200
How are you?

419
00:23:59,867 --> 00:24:00,867
<i> How are you doing?</i>

420
00:24:07,833 --> 00:24:09,967
I'm just getting started, Chief.

421
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:11,600
I'm getting his trust

422
00:24:12,767 --> 00:24:14,800
so I can get to know all about
his secrets.

423
00:24:14,933 --> 00:24:16,367
Just be careful, okay?

424
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:19,633
He can't find out that
you're working undercover.

425
00:24:19,767 --> 00:24:21,300
Maybe he's just testing you.

426
00:24:21,433 --> 00:24:22,300
Possible,

427
00:24:23,367 --> 00:24:25,933
aside from the flies
that are whispering to him.

428
00:24:26,067 --> 00:24:29,800
Based on Selena's tip,
Amo has a spy here with us.

429
00:24:29,967 --> 00:24:33,933
What I need to know is if he
is really Amo's spy or not.

430
00:24:34,067 --> 00:24:36,233
With all the rumors about Amo,

431
00:24:36,367 --> 00:24:40,467
It might just be a demolition
job.

432
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:46,133
Okay, Sir, I'll update you if I
find any leads on those cases.

433
00:24:46,267 --> 00:24:49,133
I won't hesitate to put
my father in jail.

434
00:24:49,267 --> 00:24:50,733
Be careful there, Conde.

435
00:24:51,767 --> 00:24:52,900
Update me.

436
00:24:53,033 --> 00:24:56,233
Okay, go ahead, Ms. Tess.
Thank you very much.

437
00:24:56,367 --> 00:24:57,667
Okay, okay, okay.

438
00:25:22,033 --> 00:25:23,667
It's a miracle, you're the one
calling now.

439
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:24,900
Wait, not here, not here.

440
00:25:25,033 --> 00:25:26,367
It's hard to talk here.

441
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:27,933
Your policeman is here.

442
00:25:28,067 --> 00:25:29,333
Let's just meet.

443
00:25:29,467 --> 00:25:30,633
Sir, we have another problem.

444
00:25:30,767 --> 00:25:31,700
What's that?

445
00:25:31,833 --> 00:25:35,167
One of your policemen is
hot-blooded towards Amo,

446
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:36,167
it's Enriquez.

447
00:25:36,333 --> 00:25:37,500
You know what you're going
to do, right?

448
00:25:37,633 --> 00:25:38,967
Just distract them.

449
00:25:39,100 --> 00:25:40,100
Where are you going?
What are you going to do?

450
00:25:40,233 --> 00:25:41,533
I'm nervous.

451
00:25:41,667 --> 00:25:43,167
This is my first time
pretending.

452
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:44,367
What's the first time?

453
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:46,667
We've been pretending
all our lives.

454
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:49,600
We even worked as Tanods,
will you get nervous now?

455
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:52,133
Enriquez?

456
00:25:52,267 --> 00:25:52,767
Sir...
